    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Comics whose stories are set in distant times and lands, either past or future, featuring heroic persons, magicians, and mythological figures battling evil forces, typically in face-to-face combat with swords, axes, hammers, and other hand-wielded weapons, and often involving magic.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cómics cuyos relatos transcurren en épocas y tierras distantes, en el pasado o en el futuro, que presentan personajes heroicos, magos y figuras mitológicas luchando contra las fuerzas del mal, generalmente en combates cara a cara con espadas, hachas, martillos y otras armas esgrimidas a mano y a menudo incorporando magia.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stripverhalen die zijn gesitueerd in verre streken in een ver verleden of een verre toekomst, waarin heldhaftige personen, tovenaars en mythologische figuren strijden tegen boze krachten, meestal in gevechten van man tegen man met zwaarden, bijlen, strijdhamers en andere handwapens, vaak met gebruikmaking van toverij.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000120595/Wikipedia (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>故事設定於遙遠時空的漫畫，背景可為過去或未來，以對抗邪惡勢力的英雄人物、巫師和神話人物為主角。主角在面對面搏鬥時，通常使用劍、斧、鎚和其他手持武器，且常有魔法涉入戰鬥之中。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Comic, dessen Geschichte in weit entfernten Ländern und vergangenen oder zukünftigen Zeiten angesiedelt ist, mit heldenhaften Figuren, Magiern und mythischen Charakteren, die gegen die Kräfte des Bösen kämpfen, üblicherweise in direkten Konfrontationen mit Schwertern, Äxten, Hämmern und anderen leichten Waffen, häufig verbunden mit Magie.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
